  Let me see that thing. Wow.

00:20.321 --> 00:22.388
How did you know?

00:22.389 --> 00:24.456
            He asked me if women
          know their ring sizes.

00:24.458 --> 00:26.325
               And i was like...

00:26.327 --> 00:29.328
                   "of course. I
                    mean, i do."

00:29.330 --> 00:32.197
Real smooth.
                      (chuckles)
                      so smooth.

00:32.198 --> 00:36.635
You know, i'd almost lost faith
until you guys.

00:36.637 --> 00:38.504
Maybe there's still hope
for me.

00:38.506 --> 00:40.539
      Let me see it again.

00:40.541 --> 00:43.542
Aw...
Wow.

00:43.544 --> 00:46.345
It's gorgeous.

00:46.347 --> 00:48.347
           Whoa. Hey.

00:48.349 --> 00:50.582
         Are you okay?

00:51.352 --> 00:53.419
Rose.

00:54.688 --> 00:57.289
    I've got a bad feeling.

00:57.291 --> 00:58.524
      His name was death.

00:58.526 --> 01:00.292
And hell
followed

01:00.294 --> 01:01.527
           With him.
           (gunshots)

01:01.529 --> 01:04.063
Oh, my god!
Rose!

01:04.065 --> 01:06.732
          Rose! Rose!

01:06.734 --> 01:08.467
             Rose!

01:08.469 --> 01:10.402
Somebody get a doctor out here!

01:10.404 --> 01:11.437
                            Man:
     We've got a gunshot victim!

01:11.439 --> 01:13.439
Rose! Hey, hey,
hey, hey, rose.

01:13.441 --> 01:15.441
Stay with me.
Stay with me.

01:15.443 --> 01:18.143
I got you.
Somebody help!

01:18.145 --> 01:20.212
Help!

01:32.460 --> 01:35.394
 (rock music playing on radio)

01:35.396 --> 01:39.264
     ♪ the only difference
          is a name ♪

01:39.266 --> 01:42.401
    ♪ everything around here
        feels the same ♪

01:42.403 --> 01:44.636
       ♪ procrastination,
      always waiting... ♪

01:49.410 --> 01:52.411
         Were you nice?
    You said you'd be nice.

01:52.413 --> 01:53.996
              He said that we're
                looking for e.T.

01:53.997 --> 01:55.580
    In the middle of a budget
  crisis. That's what he said.

01:55.583 --> 01:58.117
      So you weren't nice.
                      (chuckles)
                     i just made

01:58.119 --> 01:59.585
                One observation.
                    That was it.

01:59.587 --> 02:01.587
         You know, that i'm sure
          he's just as qualified

02:01.589 --> 02:03.655
          To judge the work of a
       team of radio astronomers

02:03.657 --> 02:05.557
As he is to hold public office.

02:05.559 --> 02:06.458
       I'm really worried
   about where this is going.

02:06.460 --> 02:08.127
     His daddy's oil money

02:08.128 --> 02:10.461
    Obviously qualifies him
           for both.

02:10.464 --> 02:12.231
You said that to him?
You said those words to him?

02:12.233 --> 02:14.500
                Vera, the man is
             a u.S. Congressman.
The man is an idiot.

02:14.502 --> 02:16.201
              An idiot who holds
              the purse strings!

02:16.203 --> 02:17.870
        (rapid beeping)

02:23.777 --> 02:25.477
             Vera:
             What?

02:25.479 --> 02:27.146
                   Whoa.

02:27.148 --> 02:29.214
    (men yelling in spanish)

02:34.488 --> 02:36.889
     (shouting in spanish)

02:42.329 --> 02:43.362
           (gunshot)

02:44.765 --> 02:45.697
           (gunshot)

02:46.867 --> 02:49.468
           (panting)

03:00.681 --> 03:03.415
       <i> ¿qué pasó, amigo?</i>

03:03.417 --> 03:04.783
What the hell
took you guys so long?

03:04.785 --> 03:07.452
  Five years underwater, man.
       My cover's blown.

03:07.454 --> 03:08.754
I got what we need. Now i'm out.

03:08.756 --> 03:09.955
   You hear me? I'm finished.

03:09.957 --> 03:12.624
 We got you, okay? Don't worry.

03:12.626 --> 03:14.593
You're out. We get it.
That's why we're here.

03:14.595 --> 03:16.328
             We're gonna get you
         back across the border.

03:16.330 --> 03:19.331
No. Not just across the border.
       You take me home.

03:19.333 --> 03:21.333
I'm done.
          Absolutely.

03:21.335 --> 03:23.602
         You earned it.

03:23.604 --> 03:26.605
         We got el jefe
       over a barrel now.

03:26.607 --> 03:29.975
You did get
the coordinates, right?

03:29.977 --> 03:31.643
                     Yeah, i got
                the coordinates.

03:31.645 --> 03:33.612
                      Shipment's
                   on the plane.
    Ha.

03:33.614 --> 03:37.616
You are one hell
of an agent, amigo.

03:37.618 --> 03:39.685
(children laughing, chattering)

03:45.593 --> 03:48.527
Wow. You're getting good
at those sunrises, van gogh.

03:48.529 --> 03:51.396
          I don't want to be van
       gogh. He cut off his ear.

03:51.398 --> 03:53.332
Oh, and your ears
are so cute, too.

03:53.334 --> 03:56.902
        (phone ringing)
           (chuckles)
 in the car, kiddo. Buckle up.

03:56.904 --> 04:00.472
Hello?

04:00.474 --> 04:01.473
              Amy.

04:01.475 --> 04:02.608
                           Okay,
                          mommy.

04:02.610 --> 04:04.676
       Hello. Who's this?

04:08.749 --> 04:11.483
            Ronnie.

04:11.485 --> 04:14.053
 Ronnie, if that's you, i swear

04:14.054 --> 04:16.622
I know what you are trying to do
 and she is not going with you.

04:16.624 --> 04:19.324
          You hear me?

04:19.326 --> 04:22.861
As long as i live, never again.

04:26.634 --> 04:28.700
        I'm hanging up.

04:30.738 --> 04:32.804
 (jazzy music playing on piano)

04:34.608 --> 04:36.842
           Director:
    One minute to showtime,
           preacher.

04:37.911 --> 04:40.312
     You're gonna kill it.
         You always do.

04:40.314 --> 04:41.580
       It's like opening
        for the stones.

04:41.582 --> 04:42.648
           (chuckles)

04:42.650 --> 04:45.751
      You are just as good
        as your father.

04:45.753 --> 04:47.753
                        Besides,

04:47.755 --> 04:50.422
Jagger's getting old. It's time
    for the next generation.

04:50.424 --> 04:51.757
           (chuckles)

04:51.759 --> 04:54.026
Shouldn't you
be sitting? The doctor...

04:54.028 --> 04:55.661
      Does not know squat.

04:55.663 --> 04:58.297
                Come on.

04:58.299 --> 05:00.699
       30 seconds to air.

05:00.701 --> 05:03.669
   Hey, you could be onstage
          with my dad.

05:06.740 --> 05:08.674
The view's better
from back here.

05:08.676 --> 05:11.443
Go on, preacher man.
Knock 'em dead.

05:13.447 --> 05:15.647
    (cheering and applause)

05:15.649 --> 05:17.783
       We're on in five,

05:17.785 --> 05:20.419
         Four, three...

05:20.421 --> 05:23.488
    (rock music intro plays)

05:24.792 --> 05:28.593
 Does god want us to fear him?

05:28.595 --> 05:29.795
           Audience:
              No!

05:29.797 --> 05:32.431
    Is that what you think?
           Audience:
              No!

05:32.433 --> 05:35.934
No. No, i don't think so either,
            friends.

05:35.936 --> 05:38.670
                See, my father's
     teachings show us that god,

05:38.672 --> 05:40.472
Well, god just wants us to love.

05:40.474 --> 05:42.874
  Yes, he does. Yes, he does!

05:42.876 --> 05:44.810
   He just wants us to love.

05:44.812 --> 05:46.678
           (applause)

05:46.680 --> 05:49.014
         Now, i ask you
    to remember john 10:10.

05:49.016 --> 05:52.084
          "i have come
    that they may have life

05:52.086 --> 05:54.386
   "and that they may have it

05:54.388 --> 05:57.456
        More abundantly,
       more abundantly."

05:57.458 --> 05:59.524
    (speaking indistinctly)

06:11.972 --> 06:14.639
      (continues speaking
         indistinctly)

06:21.382 --> 06:23.448
      (school bell rings)

06:24.385 --> 06:26.451
      (indistinct chatter)

06:35.462 --> 06:37.062
Girl:
Hey.

06:37.064 --> 06:39.030
Hey, peter.

06:39.032 --> 06:41.032
             Hello?

06:41.034 --> 06:42.434
             Peter.

06:42.436 --> 06:45.036
                Space cadet. Are
             you even listening?

06:45.038 --> 06:46.705
          What? Sorry?

06:46.707 --> 06:48.173
           I'm trying to ask you

06:48.175 --> 06:49.975
          When you're heading to
        lindsey's party tonight.

06:49.977 --> 06:51.977
Oh, yeah, um,
uh, i don't know.

06:51.979 --> 06:53.712
I don't think
i'm gonna go.

06:53.714 --> 06:55.714
Just be too...

06:55.716 --> 06:57.582
                Uh, too...

06:57.584 --> 06:59.584
       Much fun? Come on, peter.

06:59.586 --> 07:01.119
                  You can't swim
                 laps all night.

07:01.121 --> 07:05.724
          And, besides, i wanted
           you to drive me home.

07:05.726 --> 07:06.958
Hey, petey.

07:06.960 --> 07:09.795
You know, hanging out
with this chick,

07:09.797 --> 07:11.496
   It ain't fooling anybody.

07:11.498 --> 07:13.632
            Hey, sam, is it true
                  susan broke up

07:13.634 --> 07:14.966
    With you 'cause you have
       a really small...

07:14.968 --> 07:16.435
     You'd better shut up.

07:16.437 --> 07:17.636
                  ...Vocabulary?

07:17.638 --> 07:19.971
                 I was gonna say
                   "vocabulary."

07:19.973 --> 07:22.908
                 You think i was
          saying something else?

07:22.910 --> 07:24.509
You know,
next time

07:24.511 --> 07:25.610
           I see you,

07:25.612 --> 07:27.646
You're dead.

07:28.615 --> 07:30.682
Let's go.

07:30.684 --> 07:32.617
        (rapid beeping)
are you getting it?

07:32.619 --> 07:34.519
         Yeah. Yeah, yeah, yeah.

07:34.521 --> 07:36.521
    Seriously, what is this?

07:36.523 --> 07:38.690
             Wait.

07:38.692 --> 07:41.726
            Come on. Move. Move.

07:43.697 --> 07:46.998
This thing's really close.

08:03.784 --> 08:05.650
         (distant boom)

08:19.533 --> 08:22.100
       (distorted voices)

08:29.243 --> 08:30.909
              Man:
       <i> There's a lot more</i>
       <i> at the drop site,</i>

08:30.911 --> 08:32.677
             Right?

08:32.679 --> 08:35.547
Along with some evidence that's
gonna put el jefe away for good.

08:35.549 --> 08:37.849
            Well, we got to call
                 in the location

08:37.851 --> 08:40.519
            So we can get a team
          over there right away.

08:46.093 --> 08:47.659
Hey.

08:47.661 --> 08:49.728
Hey, my man. Are you listening?

08:59.673 --> 09:00.739
                Are those fishes
                      delicious?

09:00.741 --> 09:03.742
Can we go to texas this summer?

09:03.744 --> 09:05.076
I've never been
to texas.

09:05.078 --> 09:06.745
             You haven't been to
                a lot of places.

09:06.747 --> 09:08.780
You're six.
            I know.

09:08.782 --> 09:12.584
               Well, i do have a
              cousin in houston.

09:15.322 --> 09:18.023
I'm not going to dad's anymore?

09:18.025 --> 09:20.759
          No, sweetie.

09:20.761 --> 09:23.028
Did he do something wrong again?

09:23.030 --> 09:25.096
  (audio on radio distorting)

09:35.342 --> 09:36.708
       (tires screeching)

09:36.710 --> 09:38.910
      (indistinct chatter)

10:08.642 --> 10:11.843
(preacher speaking indistinctly)

10:11.845 --> 10:14.946
     I pray you may prosper
   in all things, just as...

10:18.919 --> 10:22.120
     (high-pitched ringing)

10:27.260 --> 10:29.160
           (gasping)

10:29.162 --> 10:30.895
Man:
Joshua!

10:30.897 --> 10:32.097
            Joshua!

10:32.099 --> 10:32.964
          (murmuring)

10:33.934 --> 10:35.800
      Call 911. Get help!

10:35.802 --> 10:36.935
                 Vera.

10:36.937 --> 10:38.703
             Vera.

10:44.945 --> 10:46.344
                       Vera!

10:47.848 --> 10:50.982
           (panting):
    Hey, vera, hey. Wake up.

10:50.984 --> 10:52.884
Oh!

10:57.958 --> 10:59.691
          Oh, god, no.

11:00.994 --> 11:02.694
             Oh...

11:13.707 --> 11:15.940
           (panting)

11:23.250 --> 11:24.949
                 Joshua. Joshua.
           Did someone call 911?

11:24.951 --> 11:26.418
            What's going on?

11:27.688 --> 11:28.987
 I don't think he has a pulse.

11:31.892 --> 11:34.459
Maybe it was
a heart attack.

11:39.733 --> 11:40.899
                        Michael!

11:42.202 --> 11:44.703
       (panting):
        Vera...

11:44.705 --> 11:47.972
Are you okay?
             I'm fine, i'm fine.
                  I must have...

11:47.974 --> 11:50.408
      Must have been dehydrated.
Okay, hold on,
just stay sitting.

11:50.410 --> 11:53.011
I called 911.
         No, no, call them back.

11:53.013 --> 11:55.013
               I'm fine.

11:55.015 --> 11:56.915
Are you sure?
   Yeah, i'm fine, i'm fine.

11:56.917 --> 11:58.249
Because my name's alan.

11:58.251 --> 12:02.053
When you woke up,
you said "michael."

12:02.055 --> 12:04.139
 Look, we have to go figure out
      what the hell it was

12:04.140 --> 12:06.224
That fell down over the horizon.
No, just take a second.
I'm gonna grab you some water.

12:06.226 --> 12:08.760
Just...
                  Let's go.

12:08.762 --> 12:11.996
         (siren blares)
   (indistinct radio chatter)

12:11.998 --> 12:14.399
Easy. Let me get
the legs free.

12:18.038 --> 12:19.504
           What are her vitals?

12:19.506 --> 12:22.273
  Nothing. She's gone.

12:22.275 --> 12:24.909
       (gasping breaths)
stay down!
Don't move!

12:26.079 --> 12:28.079
       Amy. Where's amy?

12:28.081 --> 12:30.215
      Where's my daughter?
       Where is she? Amy?
Ma'am, please!

12:30.217 --> 12:32.350
      Amy!

12:32.352 --> 12:34.753
           Paramedic:
  Female, critical condition.

12:34.755 --> 12:38.056
          Let go! Amy!
Please, ma'am,
come back.

12:38.058 --> 12:40.425
              Man:
       Get us some help!

12:45.799 --> 12:47.132
                      (coughing)

12:49.069 --> 12:51.369
           (coughing)

12:55.242 --> 12:56.875
           Let's go.

12:57.778 --> 12:59.010
       What the hell?

12:59.012 --> 13:01.112
         What happened?

13:01.114 --> 13:03.948
       We thought you were dead.

13:03.950 --> 13:06.818
    (high-pitched whirring)
        (grunts in pain)

13:06.820 --> 13:09.087
          Male voice:
    <i> Remember the training. </i>
      You all right there?

13:09.089 --> 13:11.956
    <i> It's three to the chest.</i>

13:11.958 --> 13:14.092
            What's wrong, buddy?

13:14.094 --> 13:16.261
           It's just a headache.

13:16.263 --> 13:18.730
         Nah, you're all right--
     it's just been a tough day.

13:18.731 --> 13:21.198
     Male voice: <i> Isabel...</i>
  <i> We're doing this for you. </i>
        (groans in pain)

13:21.201 --> 13:24.102
     <i> Three to the chest. </i>
     Who's... Who's isabel?

13:24.104 --> 13:25.804
            Isabel?
  What are you talking about?

13:25.806 --> 13:28.106
  She's my wife. How the hell
     do you know her name?

13:28.108 --> 13:29.107
                Whoa, slow down,
                      slow down.

13:29.109 --> 13:30.809
We're all on the same team here.

13:30.811 --> 13:32.143
               You're gonna kill
                 me, aren't you?

13:32.145 --> 13:33.845
              Three shots to the
                   chest, right?
No,

13:33.847 --> 13:34.846
   Nobody's killing anybody.

13:34.848 --> 13:36.114
He knows--
what's it matter?

13:36.116 --> 13:37.849
  Yeah, we're gonna kill you.

13:39.019 --> 13:41.186
           You want to do this?!

13:41.188 --> 13:43.087
                 Just let me go.

13:43.089 --> 13:45.824
                            Man:
                No! Don't do it!

13:45.826 --> 13:48.059
      (gunshots, grunting)

13:51.298 --> 13:53.898
         (crows cawing)

14:00.841 --> 14:02.173
           (gasping)

14:02.175 --> 14:04.843
              (panting)
baby! What happened?

14:04.845 --> 14:06.544
Are you okay?
Hey, talk to me.

14:06.546 --> 14:07.846
Baby, what's wrong?
What happened?

14:07.848 --> 14:10.548
                     Talk to me.
We thought you were gone.

14:10.550 --> 14:12.450
  I need to make a broadcast.

14:12.452 --> 14:13.885
            Tonight.

14:13.887 --> 14:16.888
Anything, son.

14:16.890 --> 14:19.123
We must share our miracle.

14:25.165 --> 14:26.564
             Excuse me.

14:26.566 --> 14:29.500
  Hey, can you... Can you please
        tell me what's going on?

14:29.502 --> 14:31.569
    She's still in surgery.

14:31.571 --> 14:34.005
We'll know
something soon.

14:37.077 --> 14:39.477
          Where the hell is she?
                Where's amy?

14:39.479 --> 14:42.080
                       It was an
                       accident.

14:42.082 --> 14:44.983
                   It was...
Nothing's ever
your fault, is it?

14:46.953 --> 14:49.087
        Our daughter is in here,

14:49.089 --> 14:51.089
        And this is what you do?
 You did this!

14:51.091 --> 14:53.458
            Ronnie:
         You did this!
 She's in here because of you!

14:53.460 --> 14:56.194
 The police report's gonna say
       you were drinking,

14:56.196 --> 14:57.896
        Again.

14:57.898 --> 14:59.898
            But that's not true.

14:59.900 --> 15:02.934
It's true if i say it's true.

15:02.936 --> 15:04.969
          Don't do this, ronnie.
I swear to god, erin,

15:04.971 --> 15:06.905
                  If she dies...

15:15.081 --> 15:16.681
        (crying quietly)

15:16.683 --> 15:18.683
              Man:
     <i> So, i know high school</i>

15:18.685 --> 15:20.551
Can be a difficult
time, peter,

15:20.553 --> 15:23.421
And you sometimes
feel hopeless.

15:23.423 --> 15:24.689
       Hopeless?
Yeah.

15:24.691 --> 15:26.691
About the present
or the future.

15:26.693 --> 15:29.994
     Is this how you interrogate
        people who almost drown?

15:29.996 --> 15:33.498
Your previous suicide attempt
is in your file, peter.

15:33.500 --> 15:35.066
   That was a long time ago.

15:35.068 --> 15:37.268
    It doesn't have anything
       to do with today.

15:37.270 --> 15:38.937
             I was swimming, and
          the next thing i know,

15:38.939 --> 15:39.938
          I'm coughing up water.

15:39.940 --> 15:41.706
           That's the end of it.

15:41.708 --> 15:44.409
                 I have practice
                tomorrow, early.

15:44.411 --> 15:46.411
We'll need to notify
one of your parents,

15:46.413 --> 15:48.146
Then you can go.

15:49.115 --> 15:51.549
Notify the group foster home...

15:51.551 --> 15:53.618
         Where i live.

15:55.088 --> 15:57.989
                  Or is that not
                   in your file?

16:06.199 --> 16:08.266
  (bird screeches in distance)

16:22.148 --> 16:25.149
       Definitely calling
         the cops, bro.

16:25.151 --> 16:27.986
     I seem to find myself
    in need of some clothes.

16:29.422 --> 16:32.623
Not sure i can help you.

16:32.625 --> 16:34.525
         But i insist.

16:38.431 --> 16:40.064
    I understand completely.

16:40.066 --> 16:42.033
                Yes, absolutely.

16:42.035 --> 16:43.601
            Thanks.

16:43.603 --> 16:45.403
        It's so strange.

16:45.405 --> 16:47.572
             What?
            Houston says they've
           got it under control.

16:47.574 --> 16:48.706
I mean, they're 700 miles away.

16:48.708 --> 16:51.609
     So maybe they know
    something we don't.

16:51.611 --> 16:53.411
 It's a meteor event-- i mean,
 it's definitely our territory.

16:53.413 --> 16:55.413
Yeah, well, if it is
a meteor, then, you know,

16:55.415 --> 16:57.615
 It'll still be there tomorrow.
                Alan, the energy

16:57.617 --> 16:59.417
From the impact knocked me out.

16:59.419 --> 17:01.719
                   That's weird.
         Did i just try
       to advise caution?

17:01.721 --> 17:03.788
I'm sorry.
My mistake.

17:03.790 --> 17:06.089
       Whatever it is...

17:06.092 --> 17:08.526
         We're gonna be
     the ones who find it.

17:12.732 --> 17:15.532
              ♪ ♪

17:23.510 --> 17:28.746
              ♪ ♪

17:28.748 --> 17:31.582
             Alan:
  <i> You know, vera, when i first</i>
     <i> got to you back there,</i>

17:31.584 --> 17:33.751
      Maybe it was just me
        being panicked,

17:33.753 --> 17:35.720
       But... I couldn't
        find your pulse.

